{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":892,"text":"\"Don't talk to strangers.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":4180,"text":"You have heard that phrase uttered"},{"time":6219,"text":"by your friends, family, schools and the media for decades."},{"time":10532,"text":"It's a norm. It's a social norm."},{"time":13444,"text":"But it's a special kind of social norm,"},{"time":15802,"text":"because it's a social norm that wants to tell us"},{"time":18332,"text":"who we can relate to and who we shouldn't relate to."},{"time":22796,"text":"\"Don't talk to strangers\" says,"},{"time":25300,"text":"\"Stay from anyone who's not familiar to you."},{"time":29476,"text":"Stick with the people you know."},{"time":31891,"text":"Stick with people like you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":34865,"text":"How appealing is that?"},{"time":37217,"text":"It's not really what we do, is it, when we're at our best?"},{"time":40442,"text":"When we're at our best, we reach out to people"},{"time":43226,"text":"who are not like us,"},{"time":44844,"text":"because when we do that, we learn from people"},{"time":47711,"text":"who are not like us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49980,"text":"My phrase for this value of being with \"not like us\""},{"time":54081,"text":"is \"strangeness,\""},{"time":55953,"text":"and my point is that in today's digitally intensive world,"},{"time":59853,"text":"strangers are quite frankly not the point."},{"time":63219,"text":"The point that we should be worried about is,"},{"time":65402,"text":"how much strangeness are we getting?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":68289,"text":"Why strangeness? Because our social relations"},{"time":71295,"text":"are increasingly mediated by data,"},{"time":74089,"text":"and data turns our social relations into digital relations,"},{"time":78646,"text":"and that means that our digital relations"},{"time":80995,"text":"now depend extraordinarily on technology"},{"time":84797,"text":"to bring to them a sense of robustness,"},{"time":87715,"text":"a sense of discovery,"},{"time":89302,"text":"a sense of surprise and unpredictability."},{"time":92572,"text":"Why not strangers?"},{"time":94339,"text":"Because strangers are part of a world"},{"time":96633,"text":"of really rigid boundaries."},{"time":98898,"text":"They belong to a world of people I know"},{"time":101850,"text":"versus people I don't know,"},{"time":104364,"text":"and in the context of my digital relations,"},{"time":106843,"text":"I'm already doing things with people I don't know."},{"time":110864,"text":"The question isn't whether or not I know you."},{"time":114082,"text":"The question is, what can I do with you?"},{"time":116586,"text":"What can I learn with you?"},{"time":119195,"text":"What can we do together that benefits us both?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123496,"text":"I spend a lot of time thinking about"},{"time":125858,"text":"how the social landscape is changing,"},{"time":128618,"text":"how new technologies create new constraints"},{"time":131090,"text":"and new opportunities for people."},{"time":133880,"text":"The most important changes facing us today"},{"time":136531,"text":"have to do with data and what data is doing"},{"time":139337,"text":"to shape the kinds of digital relations"},{"time":141442,"text":"that will be possible for us in the future."},{"time":143906,"text":"The economies of the future depend on that."},{"time":146139,"text":"Our social lives in the future depend on that."},{"time":149058,"text":"The threat to worry about isn't strangers."},{"time":152090,"text":"The threat to worry about is whether or not"},{"time":154202,"text":"we're getting our fair share of strangeness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157194,"text":"Now, 20th-century psychologists and sociologists"},{"time":159786,"text":"were thinking about strangers,"},{"time":161939,"text":"but they weren't thinking so dynamically about human relations,"},{"time":164676,"text":"and they were thinking about strangers"},{"time":166045,"text":"in the context of influencing practices."},{"time":168999,"text":"Stanley Milgram from the '60s and '70s,"},{"time":171747,"text":"the creator of the small-world experiments,"},{"time":173733,"text":"which became later popularized as six degrees of separation,"},{"time":176687,"text":"made the point that any two arbitrarily selected people"},{"time":180199,"text":"were likely connected from between five to seven intermediary steps."},{"time":183921,"text":"His point was that strangers are out there."},{"time":186951,"text":"We can reach them. There are paths"},{"time":188523,"text":"that enable us to reach them."},{"time":191209,"text":"Mark Granovetter, Stanford sociologist, in 1973"},{"time":194978,"text":"in his seminal essay \"The Strength of Weak Ties,\""},{"time":197776,"text":"made the point that these weak ties"},{"time":200602,"text":"that are a part of our networks, these strangers,"},{"time":203089,"text":"are actually more effective at diffusing information to us"},{"time":206081,"text":"than are our strong ties, the people closest to us."},{"time":210617,"text":"He makes an additional indictment of our strong ties"},{"time":214114,"text":"when he says that these people who are so close to us,"},{"time":216743,"text":"these strong ties in our lives,"},{"time":218676,"text":"actually have a homogenizing effect on us."},{"time":222103,"text":"They produce sameness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224938,"text":"My colleagues and I at Intel have spent the last few years"},{"time":227777,"text":"looking at the ways in which digital platforms"},{"time":230393,"text":"are reshaping our everyday lives,"},{"time":232264,"text":"what kinds of new routines are possible."},{"time":234881,"text":"We've been looking specifically at the kinds"},{"time":236177,"text":"of digital platforms that have enabled us"},{"time":238888,"text":"to take our possessions, those things that used to be"},{"time":242023,"text":"very restricted to us and to our friends in our houses,"},{"time":245145,"text":"and to make them available to people we don't know."},{"time":248967,"text":"Whether it's our clothes, whether it's our cars,"},{"time":251690,"text":"whether it's our bikes, whether it's our books or music,"},{"time":254313,"text":"we are able to take our possessions now"},{"time":257306,"text":"and make them available to people we've never met."},{"time":260737,"text":"And we concluded a very important insight,"},{"time":263548,"text":"which was that as people's relationships"},{"time":265336,"text":"to the things in their lives change,"},{"time":267877,"text":"so do their relations with other people."},{"time":271321,"text":"And yet recommendation system"},{"time":272729,"text":"after recommendation system continues to miss the boat."},{"time":277004,"text":"It continues to try to predict what I need"},{"time":279553,"text":"based on some past characterization of who I am,"},{"time":282793,"text":"of what I've already done."},{"time":285089,"text":"Security technology after security technology"},{"time":287593,"text":"continues to design data protection"},{"time":289769,"text":"in terms of threats and attacks,"},{"time":292174,"text":"keeping me locked into really rigid kinds of relations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295769,"text":"Categories like \"friends\" and \"family\""},{"time":298265,"text":"and \"contacts\" and \"colleagues\""},{"time":300742,"text":"don't tell me anything about my actual relations."},{"time":304529,"text":"A more effective way to think about my relations"},{"time":306773,"text":"might be in terms of closeness and distance,"},{"time":309465,"text":"where at any given point in time, with any single person,"},{"time":313285,"text":"I am both close and distant from that individual,"},{"time":316776,"text":"all as a function of what I need to do right now."},{"time":321284,"text":"People aren't close or distant."},{"time":323922,"text":"People are always a combination of the two,"},{"time":326983,"text":"and that combination is constantly changing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330703,"text":"What if technologies could intervene"},{"time":333143,"text":"to disrupt the balance of certain kinds of relationships?"},{"time":337120,"text":"What if technologies could intervene"},{"time":339081,"text":"to help me find the person that I need right now?"},{"time":343492,"text":"Strangeness is that calibration"},{"time":345916,"text":"of closeness and distance"},{"time":348135,"text":"that enables me to find the people that I need right now,"},{"time":352038,"text":"that enables me to find the sources of intimacy,"},{"time":355028,"text":"of discovery, and of inspiration that I need right now."},{"time":359676,"text":"Strangeness is not about meeting strangers."},{"time":361985,"text":"It simply makes the point that we need"},{"time":364180,"text":"to disrupt our zones of familiarity."},{"time":367462,"text":"So jogging those zones of familiarity is one way to think about strangeness,"},{"time":371119,"text":"and it's a problem faced not just by individuals today,"},{"time":373823,"text":"but also by organizations,"},{"time":376053,"text":"organizations that are trying to embrace massively new opportunities."},{"time":380576,"text":"Whether you're a political party"},{"time":382682,"text":"insisting to your detriment on a very rigid notion"},{"time":385550,"text":"of who belongs and who does not,"},{"time":387938,"text":"whether you're the government"},{"time":389431,"text":"protecting social institutions like marriage"},{"time":392129,"text":"and restricting access of those institutions to the few,"},{"time":396022,"text":"whether you're a teenager in her bedroom"},{"time":398430,"text":"who's trying to jostle her relations with her parents,"},{"time":401618,"text":"strangeness is a way to think about how we pave the way"},{"time":404780,"text":"to new kinds of relations."},{"time":407254,"text":"We have to change the norms."},{"time":410612,"text":"We have to change the norms in order to enable"},{"time":413642,"text":"new kinds of technologies"},{"time":415580,"text":"as a basis for new kinds of businesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418369,"text":"What interesting questions lie ahead for us"},{"time":422102,"text":"in this world of no strangers?"},{"time":424773,"text":"How might we think differently about our relations with people?"},{"time":428579,"text":"How might we think differently about our relations"},{"time":431700,"text":"with distributed groups of people?"},{"time":433792,"text":"How might we think differently about our relations with technologies,"},{"time":438233,"text":"things that effectively become social participants"},{"time":441239,"text":"in their own right?"},{"time":443313,"text":"The range of digital relations is extraordinary."},{"time":447126,"text":"In the context of this broad range of digital relations,"},{"time":451683,"text":"safely seeking strangeness might very well be"},{"time":454657,"text":"a new basis for that innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456928,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458398,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}